oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Buxton home
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Photograph of a group of people posing outside of the Mills Wells Buxton family home in Lancing, Tennessee. There is also a dog visible next to a boy (front center). Among those photographed are Mr. and Mrs. Buxton, George Buxton, Abe L. Buxton and Rebecca Davidson. This home was destroyed by a fire in the 1950s.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Houses; Families
